# Testing documented authd deployment script

[Spread](https://github.com/canonical/spread) tests must currently be run in a
VM on your local machine.

This test runs through the commands found in the [accompanying documentation
page](../landscape-script.md).

## Prerequisites

Multipass:

```sh
snap install multipass
```

Spread:

```sh
go install github.com/snapcore/spread/cmd/spread@latest
```

## Example: manual testing of authd deployment script

The documentation for the authd deployment script can be found in:

```sh
../landscape-script.md
```

The document is composed of code snippets defined in:

```sh
../code/deploy_authd/tests/deploy_authd_landscape/task.yaml
```

> Note: an alternative way of doing this would be to call a script, or several
scripts directly from `task.yaml` rather than embedding the commands.

To run the corresponding test, change into the test directory:

```sh
cd deploy_authd
```

List available tests:

```sh
spread --list
```

Before running the test, the following variables need to be defined in your
local environment for the script to configure authd and to test user login:

```sh
ISSUER_ID_SECRET='<issuer-secret>'
CLIENT_ID_SECRET='<client-secret'
SUFFIX_ALLOWED_SECRET='<suffix-secret>'
EMAIL_SECRET='<email-secret>'
```

Spawn a VM to run the available test (this takes a few minutes):

```sh
spread -vv -debug multipass:ubuntu-24.04-64:tests/deploy_authd
```

Relevant output for a successful test:

```
PASS
Provider: Microsoft Entra ID
...
... Successful tasks: 1
... Aborted tasks: 0
```

Running with `-debug` will automatically shell into the VM as root if there is
an error.

For example, say we try to install the wrong package:

```sh
apt-get install -y auth
```

Output:

```
+ apt-get install -y auth
Reading package lists...
Building dependency tree...
Reading state information...
E: Unable to locate package auth
-----
.
2025-09-25 16:34:31 Starting shell to debug...

```

Checking whether authd daemon is running:

```
</tests/deploy_authd_landscape# sudo systemctl status authd
Unit authd.service could not be found.
```
